


wget --mirror --convert-links --adjust-extension --page-requisites --no-parent URL

### Explanation of options:

 

* `--mirror` — Turns on recursion and time-stamping, sets infinite recursion depth, and keeps FTP directory listings.

* `--convert-links` — After the download, convert the links in the files to make them suitable for local viewing.

* `--adjust-extension` — Adds proper file extensions (like `.html`) to files.

* `--page-requisites` — Downloads all necessary files for displaying the page properly (CSS, images, scripts).

* `--no-parent` — Prevents downloading anything from parent directories.

 

### Example:

 

```bash

wget --mirror --convert-links --adjust-extension --page-requisites --no-parent https://example.com

